04/05/2022,748.2453 - Individual Standards Evaluated,Individual Standards Evaluated,No,05/10/2022,05/12/2022,Individual Standards Evaluated,High,Yes,"While reviewing the video, it was observed that children in care were helping to restrain another child in care.  ","An email was received on May 12, 2022 with the operations plans.  Semiannual staff training on EBI will be held no later than June 3, 2022 for all Option House employees with an emphasis placed on de-escalation and separating residents from any physical altercation.  Removing residents from the area will preclude residents from assisting staff in case a restraint becomes necessary.  Option House staff will also discuss any concerns regarding EBI, de-escalation and caregiver burn out.  There will also b e training conducted on the importance of MS and best practices. The staff involved in the incident is no longer employed.  "
04/05/2022,748.2551(c)(1) - Individual Standards Evaluated,Individual Standards Evaluated,No,05/10/2022,05/12/2022,Individual Standards Evaluated,High,Yes,"While reviewing the video, it was observed that staff immediately put a child in a choke hold without attempting a proper restraint.  ","An email was received on May 12, 2022 with the operations plans.   Semiannual staff training on EBI will be held no later than June 3, 2022 for all Option House employees.  Staff members will be instructed on best practices and proper de-escalation techniques.  Emphasis will be placed on body positioning in case a takedown becomes necessary during an incident or physical altercation.  MS will be utilized as a guideline as well as the current PAPH/EBI training to be conducted simultaneously.  The staff involved in the incident is no longer employed.  "
04/05/2022,748.2455(a)(2) - Individual Standards Evaluated,Individual Standards Evaluated,No,05/10/2022,05/12/2022,Individual Standards Evaluated,Medium High,Yes,"While reviewing the video, it was observed that staff initiated an inappropriate restraint prior to an emergency situation occurring.  ","An email was received on May 12, 2022 with the operations plans.   Semiannual staff training on EBI will be held no later than June 3, 2022 for all Option House employees.  Proper verbal de-escalation techniques, review of safety contracts and utilizing restrains as a last resort will be discussed thoroughly to prevent the need for staff member to restrain a resident.  OH does not condone the mistreatment of any resident in our care for any reason.   The staff involved in the incident is no longer employed.  "
